<item>
            <title>[BEAM-7613] HadoopFileSystem can be only used with fs.defaultFS</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-7613</link>
                <project id="12319527" key="BEAM">Beam</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;HadoopFileSystem&lt;/em&gt; creates underlying &lt;em&gt;FileSystem&lt;/em&gt; (one from org.apache.hadoop) instance during it&apos;s construction. Single &lt;em&gt;FileSystem&lt;/em&gt; instance is tied to a particular cluster (scheme + authority pair). In case we want to talk to another cluster, this fail due to &lt;em&gt;FileSystem#checkPath&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This can be fixed by using &lt;em&gt;FileSystem#get(java.net.URI, org.apache.hadoop.conf.Configuration)&lt;/em&gt; instead of &lt;em&gt;FileSystem#newInstance(org.apache.hadoop.conf.Configuration)&lt;/em&gt;{{}}&lt;/p&gt;</description>
